Theorem (3.42) “Contradiction”: p ∧ ¬ p ≡ false
Proof:
    p ∧ ¬ p
  =⟨ “Golden rule” ⟩
    p ≡ ¬ p ≡ p ∨ ¬ p
  =⟨ “Excluded middle” ⟩
    p ≡ ¬ p ≡ true
  =⟨ “Identity of ≡” ⟩
    p ≡ ¬ p 
  =⟨ “Symmetry of ≡” ⟩
    ¬ p ≡ p
  =⟨ “Commutativity of ¬ with ≡” ⟩
    ¬ (p ≡ p)
  =⟨ “Reflexivity of ≡” ⟩
    ¬ (true)
  =⟨ “Definition of `false`” ⟩
    false
    
